The sys.abort tool is used to halt execution with an error message. 
sys.append allows appending content to a file, while sys.download facilitates downloading files from a URL to a specified location, with options to overwrite existing files. 
The sys.find tool traverses directories to find files matching a specific pattern, and sys.getenv retrieves the value of environment variables. 
The sys.http.get, sys.http.html2text, and sys.http.post tools manage HTTP GET and POST requests, with html2text converting HTML content to plain text. 
sys.ls lists the contents of a directory, sys.read reads file contents, and sys.remove deletes specified files. 
sys.stat provides file statistics, sys.time.now returns the current time in RFC3339 format, and sys.write writes content to a specified file.